imctools: IMC file conversion tool to convert raw data MCD files into TIFF files
    https://bodenmillergroup.github.io/imctools/





1. Data Conversion
    - Convert MCD files to TIFF files with imctools
2. Preprocessing
    - Remove blanks (see message)
    - Normalize images
    - Denoise or filter images as needed
3. Spatial Windowing/Regional Analysis
    - sliding window approach
    - extract marker intensities and summary statistics 
      (mean, variance, correlation) per window 
4. Feature Extraction
    - compute window-level features: marker correlations,
      co-expression patterns, texture features
5. Spatial Analysis
    - Analyze spatial patterns, gradients, or regional heterogeneity
    - cluster window-level features 